        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Calculate the full sequence:</strong> Don't just compare play scores — calculate score + going-out bonus for each candidate. A lower-scoring play that ends the game often wins.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Dump hard tiles early:</strong> As the bag thins (under 10 tiles), play your Q, V, W, and duplicate vowels. Getting stuck with them costs double their face value.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Count remaining tiles before every play:</strong> Know exactly how many tiles your opponent has. If they have 2 tiles left, they can go out next turn — block or go out yourself.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>When ahead, close; when behind, open:</strong> Leading? Block premium squares and play tight. Losing? Open lanes and swing for the fences. Match your board strategy to your position.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>The 2-tile trick:</strong> If you can play out in one move using all remaining tiles, it's almost always correct — even for just 8 points. The going-out bonus makes it mathematically superior.</span></li>
      </ul>

